description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, dynamic and motivated band 5 Registered Nurse to join a developing Unscheduled Care team within Tawe Clinic. This role will be predominantly based on Fendrod Ward which is an all male Acute Assessment ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to undertake the role of key nurse for individual patients providing assessment, implementation and evaluation of individuals patient centred care and treatment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will form part of the multidisciplinary team to ensure an excellent standard of care is provided which is collaborative, evidence based and recovery focused.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates are encouraged to contact the ward manager to discuss the post further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Janine JohnWard Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;janine.john@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01792 516406&lt;/p&gt;
